{
  "texts": [
    "We will discuss the components in details in Section 4.",
    "Our contributions are as follows.",
    "First, we present a novel detection system capable of detecting different types of hallucinations with high accuracy.",
    "The system operates in real-time (low latency) and is suitable for large-scale applications (low cost).",
    "This approach leverages multiple hallucination detection methods-including named entity recognition (NER), natural language inference (NLI), and span-based detection-and ensembles multiple AI feedbacks using Gradient Boosting Decision Trees (GBDT)."
  ]
}